<h1>Cambridge University information</h1>
Although this site is largely about the wonders of our natural world - 
  and encouraging as many people as possible to go out and enjoy them - 
  we also have another mission. There are many bright, capable children out there 
  who do not consider going to University to study science subjects for a number 
  of reasons. We want to encourage you to think about how University could help 
  you to find a job, how you could spend another three years learning about your 
  favourite subject, how studying will bring new discoveries every day -
  go on, it's worth thinking about!
  <br>
  <br>
  rEvolution was initiated by the University of Cambridge, and so many of the 
  links below refer to Cambridge. We have had a lot of help from people working 
  in the departments of the University, and everyone we have spoken to is very 
  keen to attract people into studying the "Natural Sciences". This 
  includes Biology, Botany, Zoology, Geology (sometimes called Earth Sciences) 
  and Biotechnology.
  <br>
  <br>
Here are a few links to help you find out information about the University 
  before you apply, as well as where to go to find help and support once you are 
  there.
