<h2>Places to go for help (once you're at Cambridge)</h2>
<a href="http://www.admin.cam.ac.uk/offices/accommodation/intro.html" target="_blank">The University Accommodation 
service</a> helps students to find a place to stay if they decide to move out of their 
College. However, the vast majority of students at Cambridge will be accommodated 
within their College at least for the first year. 
<br>
<br>

<a href="http://www.admin.cam.ac.uk/about-off.html" target="_blank">The University Administration office</a> 
  contains the people who have the huge task of actually ensuring the smooth running 
  of the University. It is always a good place to start looking for help and advice; 
  if the department can't help you, they will surely know who can.
  <br>
  <br>
  
<a href="http://www.careers.cam.ac.uk/" target="_blank">The excellent Careers Service</a>  is one of the 
  reasons that 98% of Cambridge graduates are employed within a year of leaving 
  the University. The staff run a truly amazing number of events, talks, careers 
  fairs and face-to-face interviews over the year, as well as providing a comprehensive 
  library of careers resources.
  <br>
  <br>
  
<a href="http://www.cam.ac.uk/cs/ " target="_blank">The Computing Service </a> oversees computing facilities 
  throughout the University and provides a range of services from training to 
  accounts for students. The first place to go if you have any technical problems.
 <br>
 <br>
 
<a href="http://www.cam.ac.uk/cambuniv/disability/" target="_blank">The Disability Resource Centre</a> provides facilities and support for any student with difficulties, including 
  limited places in purpose-built accommodation units.
  <br>
  <br>
  
<a href="http://www.sport.cam.ac.uk/" target="_blank">The Sports department</a> - The University has a huge range of sports and 
  leisure facilities, and each of the Colleges has their own facilities as well. 
  There are many clubs to join from the traditional rowing to the unusual Ultimate 
  Frisbee, so there is no excuse for not getting involved!
  <br>
  <br>
  
<a href="http://www.lib.cam.ac.uk/" target="_blank">The University Library</a>  is one of the largest University 
  libraries in the country, as well as being a copyright library. New technology 
  allows you to search through books held in departments and colleges too to find 
  that elusive book.
  <br>
  <br>
  
<a href="http://www.cam.ac.uk/cambuniv/linkline/" target="_blank">LinkLine</a> is a voluntary counselling 
